status: MARC21-007: Specific material designation of globe
Special class of material (usually the class of physical object) to which an item belongs, e.g., a celestial globe.

definition (en): Model relating to the sky of visible heavens (sun, stars, etc.) depicted on the surface of a sphere.
Lunar globe (other than Earth) or a moon depicted on the surface of a sphere.
Model of the Earth depicted on the surface of a sphere.
Model of the Earth's moon depicted on the surface of a sphere.
Specific material designation other than celestial globe, planetary or lunar globe, terrestrial globe, Earth moon globe.
